sing the driver and what happens if the class is loaded but not registered. In that case, using `getConstructor` and `newInstance` might be necessary to ensure it works correctly. It's crucial to confirm that this setup supports the inherited `acceptsURL` method. Would a test-defined subclass of an external driver be feasible here? After all, `DriverDataSource` supports any driver class, so I should be able to work with that flexibility.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Uo6MPO32wGKk0Z86AKROxutW|fc_0de03c58d7744231016a29b9a6b87c81979944db3fcd561f5b", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.typesafe.slick/slick_3/3.6.1/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_slick/slick_3/DriverDataSourceTest.scala", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_typesafe_slick.slick_3\n\nimport java.sql.Connection\nimport java.sql.ResultSet\nimport java.sql.Statement\n\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\nimport slick.jdbc.DriverDataSource\n\nclass NonRegisteringH2Driver extends org.h2.Driver\n\nclass DriverDataSourceTest {\n  @Test\n  def loadsAndInstantiatesUnregisteredDriverClass(): Unit = {\n    val databaseName: String = \"driver_data_source_test_\" + System.nanoTime()\n    val dataSource: DriverDataSource = new DriverDataSource(\n      url = s\"jdbc:h2:mem:$databaseName;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\",\n      driverClassName = classOf[NonRegisteringH2Driver].getName\n    )\n\n    val connection: Connection = dataSource.getConnection\n    try {\n      val statement: Statement = connection.createStatement()\n      try {\n        val resultSet: ResultSet = statement.executeQuery(\"select 42\")\n        try {\n          assertThat(resultSet.next()).isTrue\n          assertThat(resultSet.getInt(1)).isEqualTo(42)\n          assertThat(resultSet.next()).isFalse\n        } finally {\n          resultSet.close()\n        }\n      } finally {\n        statement.close()\n      }\n    } finally {\n      connection.close()\n      dataSource.close()\n    }\n  }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/com.typesafe.slick/slick_3/3.6.1/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_slick/slick_3/DriverDataSourceTest.scala\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage com_typesafe_slick.slick_3\\n\\nimport java.sql.Connection\\nimport java.sql.ResultSet\\nimport java.sql.Statement\\n\\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\\nimport slick.jdbc.DriverDataSource\\n\\nclass NonRegisteringH2Driver extends org.h2.Driver\\n\\nclass DriverDataSourceTest {\\n  @Test\\n  def loadsAndInstantiatesUnregisteredDriverClass(): Unit = {\\n    val databaseName: String = \\\"driver_data_source_test_\\\" + System.nanoTime()\\n    val dataSource: DriverDataSource = new DriverDataSource(\\n      url = s\\\"jdbc:h2:mem:$databaseName;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\\\",\\n      driverClassName = classOf[NonRegisteringH2Driver].getName\\n    )\\n\\n    val connection: Connection = dataSource.getConnection\\n    try {\\n      val statement: Statement = connection.createStatement()\\n      try {\\n        val resultSet: ResultSet = statement.executeQuery(\\\"select 42\\\")\\n        try {\\n          assertThat(resultSet.next()).isTrue\\n          assertThat(resultSet.getInt(1)).isEqualTo(42)\\n          assertThat(resultSet.next()).isFalse\\n        } finally {\\n          resultSet.close()\\n        }\\n      } finally {\\n        statement.close()\\n      }\\n    } finally {\\n      connection.close()\\n      dataSource.close()\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1